commit.message:
Simplify isort config using 'profile = black'

isort now has builtin support for black through its "profiles" feature.

https://timothycrosley.github.io/isort/docs/configuration/profiles/#black
Bump version to prepare for next release

Reorganize some tests into separate module

Use SimpleTestCase to reduce the overhead of using a database
transaction.

Remove unnecessary `if language` check

settings.LANGUAGE_CODE must be set in a Django application, so this
value is never empty.

Make dependency on babel optional

As far as Python packages go, babel is quite large weighing in at 29M.
This is due to it containing a very large amount of locale data.

As babel is only used by the PhonePrefixSelect, which isn't used by all
library users, make the dependency optional.

For library users that vendor or bundle django-phonenumber-field and its
dependencies, this greatly cuts down on the final size.
Fix initial value for PhonePrefixSelect and default to PHONENUMBER_DEFAULT_REGION
Add testing and support for Django 3.1

Update test matrix

- Use Python 3.8 final release.
- Add py38-dj22 entry. Support was added in Django 2.2.8.
- Remove specific version from Travis black, flake8, and isort. Travis
  now defaults to using Python 3.
- Remove Django 1.11 and 2.1 from testing. These versions are
  end-of-life. Removing them reduces testing resources and time.
Update isort usage for compatibility with 5.* series

setup.cfg: Replace BSD with MIT

LICENSE is MIT.

Use setuptools declarative configuration

The setuptools feature is documented here:

https://setuptools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/setuptools.html#configuring-setup-using-setup-cfg-files

This removes all logic from setup.py. The package data is now declared
